# Conventional Commits

This repo uses **semantic-release** with the **Angular** commit-analyzer preset. Every commit message the AI proposes (or helps the user write) must follow this format so releases version correctly.

## Format

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short description in imperative mood>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **Subject line**: imperative, lowercase after the colon, ~72 chars, **no trailing period**.
- **Scope**: optional noun in parentheses; use when it clarifies the area (`parser`, `examples`, `README`).

## Types (common)

| Type       | Use for                                              |
| ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `feat`     | New user-facing behavior or API                      |
| `fix`      | Bug fix                                              |
| `docs`     | Documentation only                                   |
| `style`    | Formatting, whitespace, semicolons (no logic change) |
| `refactor` | Internal change, same outward behavior               |
| `perf`     | Performance improvement                              |
| `test`     | Tests only                                           |
| `chore`    | Maintenance, deps, tooling (no prod code change)     |
| `ci`       | CI / workflow changes                                |
| `build`    | Build system, bundler config                         |

## Breaking changes

Use **one** of:

- `feat!: description` or `fix!: description` (breaking marker in type)
- Or a footer line: `BREAKING CHANGE: explanation`

## Project-specific release rules

These commit shapes trigger a **patch** release even when the default preset would not:

- `docs(README): ...` — patch
- `refactor: ...` — patch
- `style: ...` — patch

Prefer **`docs(README):`** (not plain `docs:`) when only the README changes and a patch release is desired.

## Examples

```text
fix: correct blur radius when spread is negative

feat(filter): add inset shadow support

feat!: drop Node 18; require Node 20+

docs(README): fix install snippet for pnpm

chore: bump devDependencies

ci: add release workflow
```

## Anti-patterns

- Vague subjects: `update stuff`, `fixes`, `wip`
- Non-conventional types: `added`, `minor fix`, `patch`
- Past tense in subject: ~~`fixed bug`~~ → `fix: resolve overflow in sdf pass`

When squashing or merging, the **final** commit message on `main` should still match this convention—semantic-release only sees merged history.
